cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.SI 

This paper deals with malware detection and classification, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of virtual machine introspection (VMI) technique and similarity measurement methods suggest that this paper may also belong to the sub-categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of virtual machines and plug-ins may also suggest a connection to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and system and information theory (cs.SI).
